-- Jackson’s ‘Hobbit’ Grosses $13 Million in Midnight Screenings
-- B y   M i c h a e l   W h i t e
-- 2012-12-14T18:15:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-14/jackson-s-hobbit-grosses-13-million-in-midnight-screenings.html
“The Hobbit: An Unexpected
Journey,” the first in Peter Jackson’s planned fantasy trilogy,
generated $13 million in midnight ticket sales for Warner Bros.
and partner Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc.  The movie, which opened today, grossed an average $4,193
per theater in North American locations, Hollywood.com Box-
Office said today in an e-mailed statement, citing data from
 Time Warner Inc. (TWX) ’s Warner Bros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
